{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"reasoning","text":"**Analyzing potential memory leak**\n\nI'm checking the seasons endpoint and suspect that there might be a memory leak happening. It could be because the decode dimensions are set too high, like 300 parameters being ignored by the server. I wonder if it's returning a giant 4K image, but with a decode cap of 1920, it should be manageable. If each image is 1920x1080 RGBA, that's around 8MB. I'll also consider a cache limit of maybe 10 items for memory management."}}
