{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating memory issues**\n\nI’m considering whether memory might jump because `get_seasons` returns many episodes without filtering for Season types. If the endpoint returns thousands of episodes, it could really overload memory when items_to_media_items tries to load all those posters. I think I should verify this by checking the current series in log selection, maybe running a quick API call to navigate the details. Limiting the seasons call to only \"Season\" types might help fix this issue. Also, it’s important to consider loading seasons lazily to avoid memory problems.\n**Improving load management**\n\nI'm considering loading data asynchronously after the details, using a timeout and avoiding images to prevent out-of-memory issues. Another solid approach could be capping the seasons count at around 60 and still not loading images. The concern here is that if I load thousands of images, it could jump to 4GB of usage very quickly. If I eliminate loading season images entirely and only load episodes as needed, that might help. Spec suggests images, but using less quality or textless alternatives could be a suitable temporary fix for now.\n**Addressing memory crashes**\n\nI’m thinking that maybe images are necessary for the home view, but the top priority is to fix crashes by limiting the number of items processed for seasons and episodes to prevent runaway memory usage. I might set a maximum cap, like MAX_DETAIL_ROW_ITEMS=50, and avoid loading images for seasons. I need to check if the episodes row loads automatically or just after selecting a season. The out-of-memory issue likely happened due to auto-loading all seasons, so I’ll apply filters to only include items where item_type is \"Season\" and limit the load. Testing logged counts should help catch any API bugs.\n**Refining the load_seasons function**\n\nI’m wondering if get_seasons might be including some missing item types, though it’s likely just \"Season.\" I should approach this minimally. Also, I think load_item_detail might be waiting for load_seasons to complete, which could cause blocking and delays in logging that the “Item detail loaded.” Maybe that’s fine, but I should consider adding a warning for suspicious counts above 200 and skip loading images. If there are more than 100 seasons, I could use an option to limit images for the first 100. It looks like patching the load_seasons function is the way to go!"}}
